 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> total_norm <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> total_norm <span class=\"pl-k\">**</span> (<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>. <span class=\"pl-k\">/</span> norm_type) </td>\n        </tr>\n    </tbody></table>\n  </div>\n</div>\n</p>\n<p>example error message can be found at<br>\n<a href=\"https://discuss.pytorch.org/t/error-when-doing-grad-clip-norm/26071/3\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://discuss.pytorch.org/t/error-when-doing-grad-clip-norm/26071/3</a></p>", "body_text": "see\n\n  \n    \n      pytorch/torch/nn/utils/clip_grad.py\n    \n    \n        Lines 31 to 34\n      in\n      1178851\n    \n    \n    \n    \n\n        \n          \n           for p in parameters: \n        \n\n        \n          \n               param_norm = p.grad.data.norm(norm_type) \n        \n\n        \n          \n               total_norm += param_norm.item() ** norm_type \n        \n\n        \n          \n           total_norm = total_norm ** (1. / norm_type) \n        \n    \n  \n\n\nexample error message can be found at\nhttps://discuss.pytorch.org/t/error-when-doing-grad-clip-norm/26071/3", "body": "see\r\nhttps://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/117885128073c9c2b32f4b33c6c79df3895b7071/torch/nn/utils/clip_grad.py#L31-L34\r\n\r\nexample error message can be found at \r\nhttps://discuss.pytorch.org/t/error-when-doing-grad-clip-norm/26071/3"}